725834f-a.title: Queens: 123rd Street - 22nd Street
725834f-a.text:
123rd Street, adjoining and at the S.E. corner of 22nd
Avenue, viewing north toward the latter and showing some
old homes and St. Johns Evangelical Lutheran Church. The
church is at the corner. The dwellings (right to left) were
owned, in 1873, by C. Piereth, P. Ulck, and J. Harrold. The
church, too, was standing in 1873.
P. L. Sperr  March 16, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS
